The method returns a 2D array `painting` that describes the finished painting.
The `painting` array does not include any parts that are not painted.
The segments in `painting` may be in any order.
Each segment in `painting` is represented by a 2-element array, where the first element is the starting point of the segment and the second element is the ending point of the segment.
The starting point of a segment in `painting` is inclusive and the ending point is exclusive.
The mixed color sets of the segments in `painting` are different.
